# Verbs and Simple Present Interrogative

Para fazer perguntas usa-se o verbo auxiliar - Do

Verbos de exemplo:
speak, think, see

Pronomes:
I, you, we, they

Do I 	 speak english?
Do I	 think too much?
Do I 	 see dead people?

Do you   speak english?
Do you	 think too much?
Do you   see dead people?

Do we 	 speak english?
Do we    think too much?
Do we 	 see dead people?

Do they  speak english?
Do they  think too much?
Do they  see dead people?

Os verbos em inglês não mudam quando são I/you/we/they no PRESENTE.

O unico caso que muda é quando usamos os pronomes:
he, she, it

Para fazer a pergunta nesses casos é usado o verbo auxiliar "does".

Does He/She/It	 speaks english
Does He/She/It 	 thinks too much
Does He/She/It 	 sees dead people

Isso no PRESENTE!!! - SIMPLE PRESENT
===================

Do 	 I 			run 	- Eu corro?
Do 	 You 		run		- Você/Vocês corre/correm?
Does He/She/It 	runs	- Ele/Ela/Isto corre?
Do   We 		run		- Nós corremos?
Do   They 		run		- Eles correm?




